==English==
{{webster}}
===Noun===
'''nog'''

#A [[wooden]] [[block]], of the size of a [[brick]], built into a [[wall]], as a [[hold]] for the [[nail]]s of [[woodwork]]. 
#One of the [[square]] [[log]]s of [[wood]] used in a [[pile]] to [[support]] the [[roof]] of a [[mine]]. 
#(Shipbuilding) A [[treenail]] to [[fasten]] the [[shore]]s. 
#Short for [[noggin]].
#Short for [[eggnog]].

===Transitive verb===
'''nog'''

# to [[fill in]], as between [[scantling]], with [[brickwork]]. 
# (Shipbuilding) to fasten, as shores, with treenails. 

----

==Dutch==
===Adverb===
'''nog'''

# [[still]]; ''hij is nog nieuw'' (he's still a newbie)
# with negation: [[yet]]: ''hij is nog niet gekomen'' (he has not come yet)
# with [[een]]: [[another]]: ''daar is er nog een'' (that's another one)

